-------------------------
BUG REPORT - BUG-003
-------------------------
Bug ID : BUG-003
Project Name : E-Commerce Application
Module : User Login
Title : Application crashes when Password field is left blank
Severity : Critical
Priority : High
Status : New
Reported By : QA Engineer
Reported Date : 14-July-2025
Environment : OS: Android 13 | Device: Samsung M33 | App Version: 2.1.0

Description:
The application crashes and closes unexpectedly when a user attempts to 
login with a valid email but keeps the password field blank.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Launch the E-Commerce Application
2. Navigate to the Login Screen
3. Enter a valid Email ID in the Email field
4. Leave the Password field blank
5. Click on the "Login" button

Expected Result:
The application should display a validation error message: 
"Password is required" and should remain on the login screen.

Actual Result:
The application crashes and closes immediately after clicking the Login button.

Attachments : Screenshot attached - Crash_Log_BUG003.png
Notes : This is a showstopper bug. Users cannot login without password.

